- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with discrete self-similar fractals and their construction using hierarchical assembly processes. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is also likely as the paper discusses local interactions between the tile components. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are possible categories as the paper involves the bottom-up growth paradigm of self-assembly, which has applications in robotics and control systems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the computational complexity of constructing these fractals using signal passing tiles.
